for the Africa-Arabia Regional Operations Centre

flowRoot.flowPara: CHAIN-REDS has laid the foundation for continued interoperability between African and European e-Infrastructures, bringing advanced services to several new communities. Operations are more easily scalable to new sites, and the development of new services is done collaboratively using state-of-the-art tools.

text.tspan: AAROC is DevOps : Everything is code.

tspan.tspan: Working, integrated services at the site
Pat on the back and coffee break.

flowRoot.flowPara: The Africa-Arabia Regional Operations Centre (AAROC) was developed during the course of the CHAIN-REDS project. Its mission is to promote and support collective, coherent and sustainable interoperability of e-Infrastructures within the region and peer infrastructures worldwide, particularly EGI.eu. AAROC provides transparent interfaces for several scientific communities to a wide variety of e-Science Services including Science Gateways, Identity Services, and heterogeneous HPC and data facilities.
Inconsistent or incorrect deployment of services breaks interoperability.
Manual configuration of services and applications is error-prone and opaque. Site operators are busy and overworked
Operators fork the repo, apply site-specific variables for the services they desire and deploy.
Come be a part of it !
